WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:04.564
NARRATOR: <i>Last week an</i> Night Court,
<i>there was trouble for the Blakes.</i>

00:04.738 --> 00:08.606
Your Honor, Mrs. Blake returned from work
and found an eviction notice on her door.

00:08.775 --> 00:13.736
I got a simple policy:
you don't pay, you don't stay.

00:14.515 --> 00:16.916
I made that up myself.

00:17.751 --> 00:19.185
We just moved here.

00:19.353 --> 00:21.048
We don't know anyone.

00:21.221 --> 00:22.518
Can't you help us?

00:23.056 --> 00:25.423
<i>And there was trouble fur the Wheelers.</i>

00:25.592 --> 00:28.892
Your Honor, the Wheelers were found
on a park bench crying.

00:29.062 --> 00:30.894
They were arrested for vagrancy.

00:31.064 --> 00:36.002
Will I ever see Disney World now, Daddy?

00:36.370 --> 00:38.634
Never, sweetheart.

00:39.606 --> 00:42.735
Never in a million years.

00:44.378 --> 00:47.370
- This took so long, I'm frightened.
- Oh, don't worry, Mrs. Blake.

00:47.548 --> 00:50.040
I have a feeling
we're about to see some magic.

00:50.417 --> 00:52.977
The State finds the defendant
guilty as charged.

00:54.087 --> 00:55.646
Ta-da.

00:55.822 --> 00:56.914
Take it easy, kid.

00:57.090 --> 00:59.821
I'll take it any way I can get it.

01:02.062 --> 01:03.188
You're a pig!

01:04.864 --> 01:07.163
Remember that lady and her kid
from last night?

01:07.334 --> 01:10.395
- Yeah.
- Kid tried to rob a liquor store on Broadway.

01:10.771 --> 01:12.762
So he got arrested?

01:13.140 --> 01:14.972
He got shot.

01:15.542 --> 01:17.271
Uh, Your Honor?

01:23.050 --> 01:25.382
If it's about the kid, he heard already.

01:25.552 --> 01:28.146
- The cops gave him a call.
- When?

01:28.322 --> 01:30.313
Few minutes ago.

01:30.624 --> 01:32.922
Right before he quit.

01:36.797 --> 01:39.459
That's right, officer.
He's been missing since last night.

01:39.633 --> 01:42.227
Let's see, he's tall, he's skinny...

01:42.402 --> 01:45.770
...he's wearing along black robe
and blue suede shoes.

01:46.306 --> 01:49.901
Oh, and there's a possibility
he's got a stuffed armadillo with him.

01:50.077 --> 01:51.738
Hello?

01:51.912 --> 01:55.314
- We get that a lot with Harry.
- Any word from the hospital, Mac?

01:55.482 --> 01:58.577
Yeah, I just talked to them.
The kid came through fine.

01:58.752 --> 02:01.221
- Oh. Oh, thank God.
- Yeah.

02:01.388 --> 02:02.651
Now the only problem is...

02:02.823 --> 02:05.884
...the one man that needs to hear that
has vanished into thin air.

02:06.059 --> 02:09.256
Mac, where is he? It's driving me crazy.

02:11.398 --> 02:13.833
Well, he's not in Manhattan.

02:14.267 --> 02:15.291
Bull.

02:15.469 --> 02:16.834
Are you all right?

02:17.437 --> 02:19.098
I checked everywhere.

02:19.272 --> 02:21.798
I checked his apartment, no luck.

02:21.975 --> 02:23.704
I checked his favorite restaurants...

02:23.877 --> 02:27.575
...all the magic shops, the toy stores,
the parks, the zoo.

02:27.748 --> 02:29.648
Is that seaweed on your lapel?

02:29.816 --> 02:33.184
You swam around the whole island,
didn't you?

02:34.454 --> 02:36.388
And the last few miles were the hardest.

02:36.556 --> 02:38.524
I felt like I was pulling a lead weight.

02:38.692 --> 02:42.424
Bull, what are those little round marks
on the back of your uniform?

02:43.063 --> 02:45.088
Tentacles?

02:48.101 --> 02:51.196
That's what they were yelling
from shore.

